gobblin.util.request_allocation

Class ResourcePool

  • java.lang.Object
    • gobblin.util.request_allocation.ResourcePool

  • public class ResourcePool
extends Object
    Represents a pool of available resources for a RequestAllocator. The resources pool is essentially a vector of doubles where each dimension represents a resource. A set of resource requests exceeds the availability of the pool if the vector sum of those requests is larger than the vector of resources in the pool along any dimension.

    • Constructor Detail

      • ResourcePool

        protected ResourcePool(Map<String,Double> maxResources,
                       Map<String,Double> tolerances,
                       Map<String,Double> defaultRequirements)
        Parameters:
        maxResources - Maximum resource availability along each dimension. Each entry in this map is a dimension. Note this is considered a soft bound (e.g. max resources may be exceeded by a tolerance).
        tolerances - The hard limit on resources availability along each dimension is set to maxResource * tolerance. The default tolerance is DEFAULT_DIMENSION_TOLERANCE. It is recommended to always have a tolerance >1, as some RequestAllocators will do unnecessary work if the soft and hard bounds are too close to each other.
        defaultRequirements - Specifies the default usage of the resources along each dimension when creating a ResourceRequirement. Default is 0.
